features: 【Better Heat Dissipation】The low-profile CPU cooler comes with a copper base, 6 heat pipes, and a 120X15mm PWM fan to ensure excellent heat transfer from the CPU.
【Low-profile CPU Cooler】Ultra-compact low-profile cooler with only 67mm total height – ideal for HTPCs, ITX, and Small Form Factor builds.
【PWM Fan】The 120x120x15mm PWM fan delivers Low-Noise for automatic speed control and ultra-quiet operation for extreme CPU cooling performance. Max. Air Flow: 67.58CFM.
【RAM Compatibility】The small-size CPU cooler provides excellent memory compatibility even in Mini-ITX motherboards.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I have an ITX build that I tried the stock cooler on from AMD and the temperature was getting far too high with overclock settings 75° Celsius I then tried the low profile knocked to a cooler also was getting way too hot I then tried the be quiet pure rock low profile cooler also was hitting those 75c degrees way too hot I then tried this ID cooling cooler I put a full thickness fan on it instead of the slim fan because my case could fit it and my temperatures are now 15 to 20 degrees Celsius cooler than they were with the previous three coolers it even keeps my temps a little cooler than the 240 mm AIO I had put on there I highly recommend this cooler it is very well made and does a fantastic job I've tried several ID cooling coolers recently and I'm very impressed with the performance for the price

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2024
reviews.reviewText: An excellent cooler, low profile, easy to assemble and extremely quiet, highly recommended.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars An effective air cooler at a rock bottom price
reviews.reviewText: ID-Cooling has been making quality PC parts for years and this is not the first item from them I have installed in my computer. I was very happy with my previous cooler from them and this one is no exception- in fact, I think I like this cooler even more because the mounting system has been improved, making it much easier and less frustrating to install. This cooler is perfect for an SFF PC case. Its short stature and small diameter allow it to fit in even the tiniest of cases. Conversely, it can also work in a full sized tower PC case, but in that case I would worry about it not having the proper amount of power. It is intended for and most at home in a small case.This is how I installed mine, in an SFF case, and I was impressed by how sleek it looked- the black, bold lines matching perfectly with my small form GPU and chosen fans. When I turned my new PC on I was further impressed by how quiet it was. Its certainly not the quietest cooler in the world (it wont be beating any Noctua coolers, for instance) but it was nearly as quiet and effective at cooling, and for less than half the price of a Noctua its a total bargain, and I am willing to sacrifice a couple dB to save $40+, and I think many others will feel the same.Yes, I am happy to recommend this ID Cooling air cooler. It has not let me down in any way, just like every other product I have from them. They truly seem to care about quality, economy, and the customer.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Installed this on a core i3 system for my HTPC system in my living room
reviews.reviewText: added this to a HTPC case in my living room. Much better than the stock intel heatsink. Keeps it cooler by about 7C which has been nice as its been sitting at 80C in my case. Now it doesnt go above 73C when watching a 4k movie from it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A truly beefy low profile cooler
reviews.reviewText: Performs shockingly well for a low profile cooler, for it's small size it packs a TON of cooling power into a small but very dense package. Has as many heatpipes as some much larger coolers and a very well designed fin stack to go with them.It is a downflow style cooler so good case ventilation will help a lot with pushing the hotter air away and giving it a fresh supply of cooler air.Compared to the stock AM4 wraith cooler, this blows it out of the water despite being smaller.An absolute king tier cooler for Mini ATI and Micro ITX builds, and from what I have tested can handle the heat pumped out by higher tier CPUs. For a midrange build this will absolutely handle a 5600x or 7600 no problems at all. Upper tier 12/13th gen i5 and i7, no sweat.The design lets it fit with any motherboards I have, low profile or taller ram.All the heatpipes cover the entire coldplate, making sure that no mater what CPU and where the package is under the IHS there will be heatpipe coverage.The low profile fan is exceptional, but if you wanted, could be replaced with any larger 120mm fan should you have the room.An absolute masterclass in design efficiency and compatibility.My new top pick for small formfactor builds not wanting to deal with an AIO.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Awesome low profile option
reviews.reviewText: I needed a low profile for my custom hp elitedesk. I've done some pretty heavy cutting mods to this thing and stuffed in a low profile rtx4060. Mounting this cooler was no different. I had to cut the original standoff mounts that the original cooler mounted to. But everything fit right in perfectly. Had to make sure to plug in the cpu power before mounting the cooler to the bracket as there is no way to get around the heatsink once the motherboard is mounted. This thing is pretty quiet even under load wich is nice. Great value low profile cooler. Side note my copy did come in kinda beat up. Two bent fins and the main heat pipes are slightly bent too. But the cooler works well anyway

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars love it, efficient and space saving!
reviews.reviewText: this cooler is housed in a 2U server chasis and still leaves lots of room. I have thick ram w/ heat syncs that are taller than normal sticks and this still has enough room to not intrude on them, the fan is very powerful yet literally produces no noise. installation was VERY easy and comes with the proper mounting kits for a variety of different sockets! heavily recommend!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for ITX systems.
reviews.reviewText: The ID-COOLING IS-67-XT is a low-profile CPU cooler that’s as sleek as a stealth bomber and as cool as a cucumber in a freezer. With its 67mm height, it’s like the limbo champion of CPU coolers, sliding effortlessly into HTPCs, ITX, and small form factor builds.The cooler boasts 6 heatpipes, which is like having a team of microscopic firefighters constantly battling the blaze of your CPU’s heat. The 120mm slim fan is the cherry on top, whispering sweet nothings to your CPU while it works its cooling magic.It supports recent Intel and AMD sockets, which is like being the United Nations of CPU coolers. It doesn’t discriminate; it just cools.In conclusion, if your CPU was a rockstar, the ID-COOLING IS-67-XT would be its favorite groupie, always there to keep it cool under the hot stage lights. So, if you’re looking for a cooler that’s low-profile in height but high-profile in performance, this might just be your ticket to an encore performance from your CPU.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on November 24, 2023
reviews.reviewText: My first unit was defective - the threads for the fan to screw into were missing (they were just holes) so I couldn't attach it.The second unit was fine but had some rough manufacturing on the metal.Neither unit came with any instructions which was very disappointing.It's not rocket science to install but it certainly would have benefited with some clear instructions.It does perform well and cools my 5800x to around 65 degrees under load while maintaining a good noise level, but I'd definitely opt to avoid ID-Cooling in the future when selecting my next cooler.
